task.summary: Default task
Fixed bug in ProblemDiffuclty report so it only counts problmes that are shown as practice problems.
Fixed null pointer bug in collabIS
Fixed null pointer bug in collabIS
Upgraded to Intellij 2016. Using Tomcat 8 and Java 8 Eliminated some hibernate dependencies and cleaned up artifacts Added Jersey RESTful framework and handle requests in /rest/MathspringService.
Added Child assent stuff
Added a new method to the MARI service for checking how many problems a student can work on in a standard
Added Pair class
Added Pair class
Added more rules and conditions to support messages that happen at BeginProblem events.
Added built-in pretests at login time.
Added Posttest and javascript form validation of pre/post test questions.

All pretest and posttest features working including warning messages about taking too long, progress bars and dynamically added buttons. This means that authoring a problem needs to have a waitTime (in seconds) to tell the system how long to wait until popping up a message. For many questions there is no correct answer. For those questions that are math and short answer is the type of the input, we can really only do a simple string comparison

added grading of pretest problems. If the answer field of the question is non-null, it will do a string match to see if the user-input matches the correct answer (note that we DO NOT USE a,b,c for multi-choice answers - it will be the actual text string that sits next to the radio button)
Made images for pretests come from blobs in the db. This meant adding a ImageFetchServlet to get them.
Made pretest problem have a -1 waitTime if its null in the db and then eliminate the popup dialogs if this is the value for the question.
Trying to fix layout problems in quickAuth
Working AffectivaService with jersey 1.9. Cannot get jersey 2.3 working
sync with master

Added some build scripts for production
fixed bugs in pedagogy parsing so it doesn't care about old fields that aren't used anymore
Fixed bug in pretestquestion so it shows answer E now. LessonXML was not being fetched from its DB table. It was getting it from the XML inside the pedagogy XML. Now we get it from DB.
fixed bugs in pedagogy parsing so it doesn't care about old fields that aren't used anymore

Fixed bugs 311 and 312 Changed ShowExample so that it uses ShowQuickAuthProblem if the problem is quickAuth and ShowHTMLProblem otherwise Added check in params.js to not do a maybeStop() call if the problem is demo or example
Fix for bug 318. TopicIntro events in eventLog are now all set to problemID = 899 a dummy problem. StudentState was not saved after being inited during EnterTutor events.
Fix for bug 317. Eliminated the close X button in the upper right of the demo-problem dialog.
FIx bug 316. ReadProblem events now correctly set the isCorrect field.

FIx bug 315. Errors surrounding the use of the Home button. Many problems were encountered including loss of probId, topicId, getting these values from the topicState rather than lessonState, etc. Added UseCases.txt to contain tests run to verify fixes work.
FIx bug 320. External activities only play once per request. After that they will not be played again.
Fixed unreported bug where MPP would cause failure when trying or resuming a topic because the last problem mode was no longer stored in the student state because it had been reset
Added extension for Jquery UI so that I can make the learning companion dialog minimize or close and then reopen automatically when it has something to say.
